- "more than the average team" means the number of top-ranked players in a team exceeds the average number of top-ranked players across all teams.

- "shine like stars on the field" refers to the players' performance metrics, specifically their average goals scored and assists;
- "applause of the audience" refers to the average ratings given by users;
- "top 10 players" means the players ranked highest based on the combination of their performance metrics and user ratings.

- 'Forwards' (FWD) are players typically responsible for scoring goals;
- '500 minutes played' is a threshold to ensure players have been involved in enough matches to provide a meaningful average;
- 'Average goals scored' is calculated by dividing the total goals scored by the number of forwards in the team who meet the playtime criteria.

- "seasoned warriors of the pitch" refers to players who have played more than 10 matches;
- "battles" refers to matches;
